				h1.articleheading how to play SILICON ARTIST
				p.articletext Silicon Artist is equal parts criminal genius and complete joke - an incredibly powerful and rich supervillain who lacks any kind of self-control. This professional con artist loves using his shapeshifting powers to harass his teammates on the Villain Underground. When playing Silicon Artist, you'll need to do the same thing to your opponent - stretch into wild directions and shapeshift to annoy them into oblivion. 

				p.articletext Silicon Artist is an aggressive combo deck that really excels against slow defensive decks. His STRETCH skill allows players to create free copies of the Utilities and Crossovers in his deck. While this is a very powerful ability, it also requires the player to think multiple turns ahead in order to get a competitive advantage. 
	
				p.articletext If you play Silicon Artist, you'll have to be comfortable planning ahead and making difficult decisions. Due to this challenge, Silicon Artist has been classified as a HARD character - meaning that new players are recommended to keep away. However if you take the time to become familiar with his deck, you'll find Silicon Artist offers a great aggressive shell with lots of explosive combo potential.
