				h2 STRECHED!
				h3 This is a copy of the Utility card to its right. When this is destroyed, place it under your character card.

				p.articletext So how does Stretch work? Strech creates STRETCHED! cards that act like exact copies of Utilities already in play. That means you could have up to 3 copies of the same card in play! To Stretch, take one of your Utilies or Crossovers that are already in play and move them one slot to the right. Then you get to place a STRETCHED! card into the now empty Utility slot. STRETCHED! cards become 1 HP Utilities if they don't have anything to copy so it's important to think about playing cards in sequence. Let's look at a few examples!

