				p.articletext Here comes the hard part. In order for Stretch to work, we need to pay close attention to which Utility slot is chosen when playing Ballooning Bicep. If we put it in the right-most Utility slot, we won't be able to shift it over and create the STRETCHED! card in its place. That's why it's always best to play Silicon Artist's Utilities in the left-most Utility slot as a default.

				p.articletext Now that Ballooning Bicep is in place, we can stretch it out by playing Impersonate. Let's make a copy. To stretch Ballooning Bicep, move it one slot to the right and put a STRETCHED! card in its place.
			
				p.articletext At the end of our turn, we have an interesting choice. Ballooning Bicep allows us to destroy it at the end of our turn in order to draw a card. That means we could also destroy our STRETCHED! card to draw a card as well! Let's look at another example of getting value out of our STRETCHED! cards.

