						img.articlevertimg.center-block(src='../../images/sa/slingshotuppercut.png')
						h4.articleskilltext Slingshot Uppercut is an Action card available in Silicon Artist's deck. Played by itself, you may choose to Stretch one of your Utilities and then deal 2 damage to any one player.

				p.articletext These two cards work quite well together. Let's walk through it. For this example, let's say we already have a STRETCHED! card in play. 

				p.articletext First, let's play a copy of Slingshot Uppercut. Although we do not have another Utility in play, we can choose to stretch our STRETCHED! card in order to create a second STRETCHED! card. With two stretched cards in play, any one single Utility or Crossover will be copied twice! The extra 2 player damage granted by Slingshot Uppercut is a nice bonus.

				p.articletext Next, let's play a copy of Bodyrang. Bodyrang also deals 2 damage to an opponent, but you can have it return to your hand by destroying one of your STRETCHED! cards when you play it. Don't be afraid to cash in your STRETCHED! cards if you can't play any Utilities! - Silicon Artist has lots of tricks to get the most out of your STRETCHED! cards.

				p.articletext Learning how to get the most of Silicon Artist's STRETCHED! cards can take some time, but making copies of powerful Utilities and Crossovers can get out of control very quickly. To set up good copies, you may have to plan a few turns ahead. Feeling pulled in too many directions with Silicon Artist? Try to take advantage of STRETCHED! cards being able to attack before the cards they copy. Aggressive Silicon Artist players can break through defensive players early!	

